Since the oxygen flux associated with the proton leak is approximately one tenth of
					, the maximal rate of oxygen consumption, the P/O ratio as a function of MVO2 is approximately expressed as P/O = 2.5 (MVO2 − 0.1
					)/ MVO2, where 2.5 is the theoretical maximum obtained by the model of oxidative phosphorylation in the absence of a leak current.

